      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks, I move SKU into Inventory.Decorator.Asset as a new property rather than a standalone interface.\n\nOn how SKU differs from PartNumber, DMTF defines them as two separate, co-existing properties on the same resource. Quoting the Chassis schema verbatim:\n\n  1.PartNumber: \"This property shall contain a part number assigned by the\n               organization that is responsible for producing or\n               manufacturing the chassis.\"\n               \n  2.SKU:        \"This property shall contain the stock-keeping unit number\n               for this chassis.\"\n\nSo PartNumber is tied to the producing/manufacturing organization, while SKU is the stock-keeping unit number. Since DMTF models them as distinct properties, SKU is added as its own property rather than reusing PartNumber.\n\nhttps://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Chassis_v1.xml\n\nPlease correct me if my understanding is off. Thanks!",
